article.description: JaKeenan Gant and Marcus Stroman each scored 21 points and Louisiana rallied late to beat Troy 86-81 in a Sun Belt battle on Saturday night.
article.headline: Gant, Stroman each score 21, lead Louisiana past Troy, 86-81
article.linkText: Gant, Stroman each score 21, lead Louisiana past Troy, 86-81
article.story: LAFAYETTE, La. -- JaKeenan Gant and Marcus Stroman each scored 21 points and Louisiana-Lafayette rallied late to beat Troy 86-81 in a Sun Belt battle on Saturday night. The Ragin' Cajuns won their second straight game, the first time they have put together back-to-back wins since they beat McNeese and Southeastern Louisiana in December. Javan Johnson made two free throws and followed them with a 3-pointer to put Troy in front, 66-62 with 8:19 left. Cedric Russell tied the game at 76-76, and after the teams traded baskets, and then Stroman put the Ragin' Cajuns in front for good with a layup. Justin Miller and Stroman each hit two free throws down the stretch to protect the lead. Gant was 4-for-4 from distance and grabbed 10 rebounds for Louisiana-Lafayette (13-7, 4-3). Stroman dished seven assists. Varnado finished with 33 points and 11 rebounds for Troy while Alex Hicks and Johnson each added 20 points.
